[Mr Ramel announces the dispatch by Mr Mueller of seeds of Palm trees that appear as though they should succeed in sheltered places on the coasts of the Mediterranean. At the same time he points out that Mr Mueller, desirous of increasing the riches of the Society’s collections, thinks that in the near future he will be able to send him living specimens of the lyre bird, because he has been able to keep for six months a female that has been kept isolated, all the while maintaining good health.





         See also M to R. Heales, 10 January 1861.


]
